Class RandomisedUrlService

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.dao.support.DaoSupport
      • org.springframework.orm.hibernate3.support.HibernateDaoSupport
        • org.sakaiproject.shortenedurl.impl.RandomisedUrlService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ShortenedUrlService, org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean

    public class RandomisedUrlService
extends org.springframework.orm.hibernate3.support.HibernateDaoSupport
implements ShortenedUrlService
    An implementation of ShortenedUrlService to provide randomised URLs

    This implementation stores the shortened key and original URL in a local database table, and uses the resolver servlet to translate the key back to it's original URL.

    URLs created are of the form: http://your.sakai.server/x/1w2Kb8

    Author:
    Steve Swinsburg (steve.swinsburg@gmail.com)

      • shorten

        public String shorten(String url)
        Generate a randomised URL for the given URL Store it and returns it or null if errors

        Defaults to short mode where keys are 6 characters long. This should be sufficient for most since the authentication is handled by the container.
        If you are passing sensitive information on an unauthenticated URL, you can use shorten(String url, boolean secure) to create a longer key.

        Specified by:
        shorten in interface ShortenedUrlService
        Parameters:
        url - - the long URL
        Returns:
        the shortened URL, or null if errors.

      • shorten

        public String shorten(String url,
             boolean secure)
        Generate a reandomised URL for the given URL but with a much longer key (22 chars vs 6 chars). Store it and return it or null if errors.
        Specified by:
        shorten in interface ShortenedUrlService
        Parameters:
        url - - the long URL
        secure - - if a longer key is required.
        Returns:
        the shortened URL, or null if errors.
